1&cid=23&frid=23&eid=126949|title=9936 Al-Qaeda-Linked Arabs Killed in Syria: Survey|accessdate=25 October 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141029174412/http://www.almanar.com.lb/english/adetails.php?fromval=1&cid=23&frid=23&eid=126949|archive-date=29 October 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> The London-based ''European Centre for Syria Research'' put the number of Saudis killed even higher at 729 a month earlier in November 2013, out of 6,113 foreign fighters reported killed by then.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://jordantimes.com/128-jordanians-slain-in-syria----report|title=128 Jordanians \u2018slain\u2019 in Syria \u2014 report|work=Jordan Times|accessdate=25 October 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150602220352/http://jordantimes.com/128-jordanians-slain-in-syria----report|archivedate=2 June 2015}}</ref> The jihadist movement updated the number of Jordanians killed by late May 2014 to 342,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://jordantimes.com/two-jordanian-jihadists-killed-in-syria|title=\u2018Two Jordanian jihadists killed in Syria\u2019|work=Jordan Times|accessdate=25 October 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140527073232/http://jordantimes.com/two-jordanian-jihadists-killed-in-syria|archivedate=27 May 2014}}</ref> although they put the figure in late October at over 250.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://jordantimes.com/at-least-250-jordanian-jihadists-killed--in-syria-since-2011|title=\u2018At least 250 Jordanian jihadists killed  in Syria since 2011\u2019|work=Jordan Times|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141029144335/http://jordantimes.com/at-least-250-jordanian-jihadists-killed--in-syria-since-2011|archivedate=2014-10-29}}</ref> According to another estimate, the Jordanian toll was at least 500 by July 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ieee.es/en/Galerias/fichero/docs_opinion/2016/DIEEEO68-2016_CombatientesJordanos_Siria_AlbertoCaballero_ENGLISH.pdf|title=Jordanian foreign fighters in Syria and Iraq: how did they become radicalized and how they can be de-radicalized?|work=|accessdate=7 July 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161124154811/http://www.ieee.es/en/Galerias/fichero/docs_opinion/2016/DIEEEO68-2016_CombatientesJordanos_Siria_AlbertoCaballero_ENGLISH.pdf|archive-date=24 November 2016|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nAccording to [[Abu Omar al-Shishani]], the Chechen [[Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant|ISIL]] commander, 500 militants from the [[Caucasus]] had been killed by mid-January 2014 since the start of the war.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.shiapost.com/2014/01/18/isil-beheads-40-members-of-rival-group-in-aleppo/|title=ISIL Beheads 40 Members Of Rival Group In Aleppo|accessdate=25 October 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140120142226/http://en.shiapost.com/2014/01/18/isil-beheads-40-members-of-rival-group-in-aleppo/|archive-date=2014-01-20|url-status=dead}}</ref> [[Ramzan Kadyrov]], [[Head of the Chechen Republic]], stated in late November 2015, that 200 Chechens had died.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sputniknews.com/military/20151116/1030163434/isil-chechens-karydov.html|title=Almost 500 Chechens Joined ISIL, Around 200 Killed - Chechnya Leader|author=Sputnik|date=16 November 2015|publisher=|accessdate=12 April 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304111011/http://sputniknews.com/military/20151116/1030163434/isil-chechens-karydov.html|archive-date=4 March 2016|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nAccording to a report by a Syrian military research center, as of September 2014: 3,872 Saudi, 3,691 Chechen and 2,904 Lebanese fighters had been killed. Another 2,689 Saudi fighters were missing.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-29043331|title=Iraq and Syria: Who are the foreign fighters?|work=BBC News|accessdate=12 April 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160409123042/http://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-29043331|archive-date=9 April 2016|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn mid-May 2015, at least 70 Lebanese fighters were reported killed in the previous several months.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailystar.com.lb/News/Lebanon-News/2015/May-11/297557-north-lebanon-isis-fighter-killed-in-syria.ashx|title=North Lebanon ISIS fighter killed in Syria|work=The Daily Star Newspaper - Lebanon|accessdate=28 October 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151019175859/http://www.dailystar.com.lb//News/Lebanon-News/2015/May-11/297557-north-lebanon-isis-fighter-killed-in-syria.ashx|archive-date=19 October 2015|url-status=live}}</ref> In late December 2015, Tunis stated 800 Tunisian ISIL fighters had been killed since the start of the war.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.abna24.com/service/middle-east-west-asia/archive/2015/12/26/726907/story.html|title=800 Tunisian jihadists killed fighting for ISIS in Syria|date=26 December 2015|publisher=|accessdate=12 April 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151230035915/http://en.abna24.com/service/middle-east-west-asia/archive/2015/12/26/726907/story.html|archive-date=30 December 2015|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe nationalities of some others are as follows: 2,960 Russians,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/wires/ap/article-3325161/Official-says-160-Russian-IS-fighters-killed-Syria.html|title=Official Says 160 Russian IS Fighters Killed in Syria|date=2015-11-19|accessdate=2015-11-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151120182612/http://www.dailymail.co.uk/wires/ap/article-3325161/Official-says-160-Russian-IS-fighters-killed-Syria.html|archive-date=2015-11-20|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rbc.ru/rbcfreenews/5a01a0329a79474ee42a1a3c|title=\u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u044f \u043e\u0442\u0447\u0438\u0442\u0430\u043b\u0430\u0441\u044c \u043e\u0431 \u0443\u043d\u0438\u0447\u0442\u043e\u0436\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0438 50 \u0442\u044b\u0441. \u0431\u043e\u0435\u0432\u0438\u043a\u043e\u0432 \u0432 \u0421\u0438\u0440\u0438\u0438 \u0437\u0430 \u0434\u0432\u0430 \u0