-regime.html |archive-date=2013-08-17 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2015/02/05/us-mideast-crisis-china-idUSKBN0L90T620150205|title=Islamic State executes three of its Chinese militants: China paper|work=Reuters|date=5 February 2015|access-date=30 June 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924213135/http://www.reuters.com/article/2015/02/05/us-mideast-crisis-china-idUSKBN0L90T620150205|archive-date=24 September 2015|url-status=live}}</ref> 3 Pakistanis,<ref name=\"shaghor\"/> 2\u20133 Filipinos,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rappler.com/nation/69817-dead-filipino-isis-jihadists|title=Filipino jihadists killed in Syria - reports|work=Rappler|accessdate=25 October 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140929164451/http://www.rappler.com/nation/69817-dead-filipino-isis-jihadists|archive-date=29 September 2014|url-status=live}}</ref> 2 Eritreans,<ref name=\"shaghor\">{{cite web|url=http://shaghor.com/index.php?s=26|title=Shaghor - Martyrs|accessdate=25 October 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006102726/http://shaghor.com/index.php?s=26|archivedate=6 October 2014}}</ref> 2 Mauritanians,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.al-monitor.com/pulse/security/01/09/moroccan-and-algerian-militants-fighting-alongside-al-qaeda-group-among-dead-in-syria.html |title=African Militants Killed in Syria Fighting Alongside al-Qaeda |publisher=Al-monitor.com |date= |accessdate=2013-08-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130921060443/http://www.al-monitor.com/pulse/security/01/09/moroccan-and-algerian-militants-fighting-alongside-al-qaeda-group-among-dead-in-syria.html |archive-date=2013-09-21 |url-status=live }}</ref> 2 South Africans,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.co.za/2017/02/17/second-south-african-reportedly-killed-in-syria-while-rebels-wa/|title=Second South African Reportedly Killed In Syria, While Rebels Want To Swop SA Journalist For Captured Rebels|publisher=|accessdate=1 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170221185606/http://www.huffingtonpost.co.za/2017/02/17/second-south-african-reportedly-killed-in-syria-while-rebels-wa/|archive-date=21 February 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> 2 Spaniards,<ref name=\"tracking\">{{cite web|url=http://www.washingtoninstitute.org/policy-analysis/view/foreign-jihadists-in-syria-tracking-recruitment-networks|title=Foreign Jihadists in Syria: Tracking Recruitment Networks|publisher=|accessdate=25 October 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141009045841/https://www.washingtoninstitute.org/policy-analysis/view/foreign-jihadists-in-syria-tracking-recruitment-networks|archive-date=9 October 2014|url-status=live}}</ref> 2 Uzbeks,<ref name=\"shuhadanationality\"/><ref name=\"onebulgarian\"/> 1 Armenian,<ref name=\"shaghor\"/> 1 Bulgarian,<ref name=\"onebulgarian\">{{cite web |url=http://paper.standartnews.com/en/article.php?d=2013-06-06&article=43126 |title=One Bulgarian among 280 Foreign Fighters Killed in Syria |publisher=Paper.standartnews.com |accessdate=2013-08-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130921055053/http://paper.standartnews.com/en/article.php?d=2013-06-06&article=43126 |archive-date=2013-09-21 |url-status=dead }}</ref> 1 Chadian,<ref name=\"names\"/> 1 Japanese,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/news/world-news/live-haruna-yukawa-isis-beheading-5035736|title=Haruna Yukawa ISIS beheading: Recap after terror group 'executes Japanese hostage'|author=Anthony Bond|date=24 January 2015|work=mirror|access-date=5 April 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180515044133/https://www.mirror.co.uk/news/world-news/live-haruna-yukawa-isis-beheading-5035736|archive-date=15 May 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> 1 Kazakh,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=72782|title=The airdrop in Beqres east of Deir Ezzor arrests a European explosive expert and Arab fighter and kills a Kazakh fighter and his family|publisher=|accessdate=5 September 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170902111254/http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=72782|archive-date=2 September 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> 1 Romanian<ref name=\"tracking\"/> and 1 Slovenian.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/08/03/middleeast/uk-syria-death-kurdish/index.html|title=British national dies fighting ISIS in Syria|first=Angela |last=Dewan|publisher=CNN|accessdate=1 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170808073355/http://www.cnn.com/2016/08/03/middleeast/uk-syria-death-kurdish/index.html|archive-date=8 August 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Foreign soldiers killed===\n\n469\u2013547 foreign soldiers have been killed during the conflict, mostly in the border areas with Syria.\n\n{{flagicon|Iraq}} '''16 servicemen killed'''<br />On 2 March 2013, one Iraqi soldier was killed during clashes between Syrian rebels and government forces at a Syrian-Iraqi border crossing.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.naharnet.com/stories/en/74130-iraqi-soldier-killed-by-fire-from-syria |title=Iraqi Soldier Killed by Fire from Syria |publisher=Naharnet.com |date=2013-03-03 |accessdate=2013-08-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130801024121/http://www.naharnet.com/stories/en/74130-iraqi-soldier-killed-by-fire-from-syria |archive-date=2013-08-01 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 4 March 2013, 13 Iraqi soldiers were killed by unknown gunmen near the border with Syria while they were transporting 65 Syrian soldiers and government officials back to their country after they had retreated to Iraq a few days earlier. 48 of the Syrians were also killed in the attack.<ref>{{cite news |last=Yacoub |first=Khaled |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2013/03/04/us-syria-crisis-idUSBRE9230S620130304 |title=At least 40 Syrian soldiers killed going home in Iraq |publisher=Reuters.com |date=2013-03-04 |accessdate=2013-08-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131015041743/http://www.reuters.com/article/2013/03/04/us-syria-crisis-idUSBRE9230S620130304 |archive-date=2013-10-15 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Donnelly |first=Thomas |url=http://washingtonexaminer.com/syrian-jets-bomb-northern-city-overrun-by-rebels/article/2523370 |title=Syrian jets bomb northern city overrun by rebels |publisher=Washingtonexaminer.com |date= |accessdate=2013-08-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130928053739/http://washingtonexaminer.com/syrian-jets-bomb-northern-city-overrun-by-rebels/article/2523370 |archive-date=2013-09-28 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 9 June 2013, Syrian rebels attacked a southern Iraqi border post, killing one Iraqi guard and wounding two.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/world/syria-rebels-fire-on-iraq/703066.html |title=Syria rebels fire on Iraq border posts, one killed |publisher=Channelnewsasia.com |date=2013-06-09 |accessdate=2013-08-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130615180738/http://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/world/syria-rebels-fire-on-iraq/703066.html |archive-date=2013-06-15 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 14 July 2013, another attack by fighters from the Syrian side of the border left one Iraqi policeman dead and five others wounded.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.presstv.ir/detail/2013/07/13/313673/syria-militants-kill-iraqi-border-guard/ |title=Iraqi border guard killed in Syria violence spillover |publisher=Presstv.ir |date=2013-07-13 |accessdate=2013-08-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130820235522/http://www.presstv.ir/detail/2013/07/13/313673/syria-militants-kill-iraqi-border-guard/ |archive-date=2013-08-20 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n{{flagicon|Jordan}} '''8 servicemen killed'''<br /> A Jordanian soldier was killed in clashes with armed militants who were attempting to cross the border from Jordan into Syria on 22 October 2012.<ref>{{cite web |author=BARBARA SURK Associated Press |url=http://www.mercurynews.com/breaking-news/ci_21826861/jordanian-soldier-killed-clash-at-syrian-border |title=Syrian violence spills into Jordan, Lebanon |publisher=Mercurynews.com |date= |accessdate=2013-08-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131003032056/http://www.mercurynews.com/breaking-news/ci_21826861/jordanian-soldier-killed-clash-at-syrian-border |archive-date=2013-10-03 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 3 January 2015, ISIL burned a Jordanian military pilot alive in a metal cage. The pilot was captured after his airplane crashed near [[Raqqa]] while conducting air-strikes.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-31129416|title=Jordan pilot murder: Islamic State deploys asymmetry of fear|date=4 February 2015|publisher=|accessdate=1 April 2017|via=www.bbc.com|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170409045100/http://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-31129416|archive-date=9 April 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> Six Jordanian soldiers were killed by a car-bomb blast near the Syrian refugee camp of al-Rukban on 21 June 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aljazeera.com/news/2016/06/jordan-soldiers-killed-syria-border-bomb-attack-160621064610938.html|title=Jordan soldiers killed in Syria border bomb attack|publisher=|accessdate=1 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170512031654/http://www.aljazeera.com/news/2016/06/jordan-soldiers-killed-syria-border-bomb-attack-160621064610938.html|archive-date=12 May 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n{{flagicon|Lebanon}} '''60 servicemen killed'''<br /> On 1 February 2013, two Lebanese soldiers were killed, along with 1-2 militants, and six were wounded in clashes near the Syrian border which started after an attempt by the military to arrest an anti-Assad rebel commander, who was also killed.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dailystar.com.lb/News/Politics/2013/Feb-02/204737-arsal-ambush-kills-two-lebanese-soldiers-hunting-w.ashx |title=Arsal ambush kills two Lebanese soldiers hunting wanted fugitive |publisher=Dailystar.com.lb |date= |accessdate=2013-08-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131014225632/http://www.dailystar.com.lb/News/Politics/2013/Feb-02/204737-arsal-ambush-kills-two-lebanese-soldiers-hunting-w.ashx |archive-date=2013-10-14 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2013/02/02/world/middleeast/syria-crisis.html|title=Soldiers in Lebanon Die in Raid Near Syria|date=2 February 2013|work=The New York Times|accessdate=12 April 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150414173221/http://www.nytimes.com/2013/02/02/world/middleeast/syria-crisis.html|archive-date=14 April 2015|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dailystar.com.lb/News/Local-News/2013/Feb-01/204650-army-patrol-ambushed-in-east-lebanon-several-casua.ashx#axzz2JfNXn2Mh |title=Four soldiers killed in east Lebanon ambush |publisher=Dailystar.com.lb |date=2013-02-01 |accessdate=2013-08-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190223131443/http://www.dailystar.com.lb/News/Local-News/2013/Feb-01/204650-army-patrol-ambushed-in-east-lebanon-several-casua.ashx#axzz2JfNXn2Mh |archive-date=2019-02-23 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 28 May 2013, three Lebanese soldiers were killed in an attack on their checkpoint near the border town of Arsal by unknown militants who then fled over the border into Syria.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2013/05/29/world/middleeast/syria.html|title=Rocket and Gun Attacks Add to Fears That Syria\u2019s Strife Is Reaching Lebanon|date=29 May 2013|work=The New York Times|accessdate=12 April 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151001033928/http://www.nytimes.com/2013/05/29/world/middleeast/syria.html|archive-date=1 October 2015|url-status=live}}</ref> On 29 March 2014, three soldiers were killed and four wounded in a suicide bomb attack on their checkpoint near Arsal.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sbs.com.au/news/article/2014/03/30/suicide-bombing-lebanon-kills-three|title=Suicide bombing in Lebanon kills three|work=News|accessdate=25 October 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141025114626/http://www.sbs.com.au/news/article/2014/03/30/suicide-bombing-lebanon-kills-three|archive-date=25 October 2014|url-status=live}}</ref> 20 soldiers were killed during the [[Battle of Arsal (2014)|Battle of Arsal]] against Syrian and other foreign jihadists and a further 13 were captured and subsequently executed. On 19 September, two soldiers were killed by a roadside bomb near Arsal.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.trust.org/item/20140919193813-jois9|title=Syria militants kill captive Lebanese soldier, bomb kills two|author=Thomson Reuters Foundation|publisher=|accessdate=25 October 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141112003918/http://www.trust.org/item/20140919193813-jois9/|archive-date=12 November 2014|url-status=live}}</ref> On 2 December, six soldiers were killed and one wounded in an ambush by unknown gunmen in the Tal Hamra area of Ras Baalbek, near the border with Syria.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aljazeera.com/news/middleeast/2014/12/lebanese-troops-killed-near-syrian-border-2014122193646646562.html|title=Lebanese troops killed near Syrian border|work=aljazeera.com|access-date=2014-12-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141209081541/http://www.aljazeera.com/news/middleeast/2014/12/lebanese-troops-killed-near-syrian-border-2014122193646646562.html|archive-date=2014-12-09|url-status=live}}</ref> On 23 January 2015, eight soldiers were killed and 22 wounded near Ras Baalbek after their outpost near the border was attacked by ISIL. The fighting also left more than 40 militants dead.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailystar.com.lb/News/Lebanon-News/2015/Jan-24/285195-lebanon-army-finds-3-more-bodies-of-soldiers-as-guns-fall-silent.ashx|title=8 soldiers dead, 22 wounded as Lebanon border battle ends|work=The Daily Star Newspaper - Lebanon|access-date=2015-01-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150128064234/http://www.dailystar.com.lb/News/Lebanon-News/2015/Jan-24/285195-lebanon-army-finds-3-more-bodies-of-soldiers-as-guns-fall-silent.ashx|archive-date=2015-01-28|url-status=live}}</ref> Three soldiers were also killed during [[Qalamoun offensive (July\u2013August 2017)|an offensive against ISIL]] in the border area in August 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-lebanon-syria/three-lebanese-soldiers-killed-in-landmine-along-border-with-syria-security-source-idUSKCN1B00G9|title=Three Lebanese soldiers killed in landmine on Syria border: security source|date=20 August 2017|publisher=|via=Reuters|access-date=16 September 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170903080953/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-lebanon-syria/three-lebanese-soldiers-killed-in-landmine-along-border-with-syria-security-source-idUSKCN1B00G9|archive-date=3 September 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n{{flagicon|Russia}} '''133\u2013156 servicemen killed'''\n{{See also|Russian Armed Forces casualties in Syria}}\n\nFollowing the start of [[Russian military intervention in Syria|Russia's intervention in Syria]] against rebel and ISIL forces at the end of September 2015, 116 soldiers had died by 23 February 2019.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://eaworldview.com/2019/03/syria-daily-russia-acknowledges-deaths-of-3-troops/ |title=Syria Daily: Russia Acknowledges Deaths of 3 Troops |access-date=2019-11-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330073541/https://eaworldview.com/2019/03/syria-daily-russia-acknowledges-deaths-of-3-troops/ |archive-date=2019-03-30 |url-status=live }}</ref> Among them, was a Russian military co-pilot who was killed when his Su-24 military plane was shot down near the Turkish-Syrian border by the Turkish military on 24 November 2015. His pilot was later recovered alive and well by Russian and Syrian special forces. Additionally, a Russian marine was killed when his military rescue helicopter was shot down by rebels while searching for the downed plane's pilots.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/russia-says-marine-killed-during-mission-to-find-downed-pilots-1448391549|title=Russia Says Marine Killed During Mission to Find Downed Pilots|author=Thomas Grove|date=24 November 2015|work=WSJ|accessdate=12 April 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160410015352/http://www.wsj.com/articles/russia-says-marine-killed-during-mission-to-find-downed-pilots-1448391549|archive-date=10 April 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> Almost half of the deaths were attributed to the crash of an [[An-26]] on approach to Khmeimim air base in Latakia, and the accidental shooting down of a reconnaissance plane by Syrian air-defenses.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tass.com/defense/1023714|title=Russia lost 112 servicemen over three years of counter-terror operation in Syria - MP|website=TASS|accessdate=19 February 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190212015832/http://tass.com/defense/1023714|archive-date=12 February 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Between 15 and 18 January 2020, 4 Russian soldiers were killed by jihadist groups in the eastern countryside of Idlib.<ref>http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=153207</ref>\n\n{{flagicon|Turkey}} '''241\u2013296 servicemen killed'''\n{{See also|Turkish Armed Forces casualties in Syria}}\nTwo members of the Turkish Air Force were killed when their F-4 Phantom II military jet was shot down near the Turkish-Syrian border by the Syrian Army on 22 June 2012.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.aljazeera.com/news/middleeast/2012/07/201274122120638820.html |title=Turkey locates bodies of downed jet pilots |publisher=Aljazeera.com |date= |accessdate=2013-08-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171010173817/http://www.aljazeera.com/news/middleeast/2012/07/201274122120638820.html |archive-date=2017-10-10 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 2 May 2013, one Turkish border guard policeman was killed in a clash with smugglers or rebel fighters on the border between Turkey and Syria. According to the opposition, two rebels were killed as well.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.worldbulletin.net/?aType=haber&ArticleID=107960 |title=Turkish police killed in clashes on Syrian border |publisher=Worldbulletin.net |date=2013-05-02 |accessdate=2013-08-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130915234625/http://www.worldbulletin.net/?aType=haber&ArticleID=107960 |archive-date=2013-09-15 |url-status=live }}</ref> Throughout 2014, seven soldiers and a policeman were killed along the border with Syria in shootouts with foreign jihadists, Kurdish fighters and other unknown gunmen.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailysabah.com/nation/2014/03/25/isil-connection-in-attack-against-turkish-security-forces|title=ISIL CONNECTION IN ATTACK AGAINST TURKISH SECURITY FORCES|work=dailysabah.com|accessdate=25 October 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160313005134/http://www.dailysabah.com/nation/2014/03/25/isil-connection-in-attack-against-turkish-security-forces|archive-date=13 March 2016|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hurriyetdailynews.com/turkish-soldier-killed-in-syria-border-clash-with-smugglers-official.aspx?pageID=238&nID=69440&NewsCatID=509|title=Third Turkish soldier dies after deadly clashes with militants on Syrian border|publisher=|accessdate=26 February 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160224183330/http://www.hurriyetdailynews.com/turkish-soldier-killed-in-syria-border-clash-with-smugglers-official.aspx?pageID=238&nID=69440&NewsCatID=509|archive-date=24 February 2016|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aljazeera.com/news/middleeast/2014/12/turkish-soldiers-killed-syria-border-201412954440122185.html|title=Turkish soldier kills comrades and himself|work=aljazeera.com|access-date=2014-12-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150403140058/http://www.aljazeera.com/news/middleeast/2014/12/turkish-soldiers-killed-syria-border-201412954440122185.html|archive-date=2015-04-03|url-status=live}}</ref> On 22 February 2015, a soldier was killed in an accident during a military incursion into Syria to evacuate Turkish troops at the [[Tomb of Suleyman Shah]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/wires/afp/article-2963690/Turkey-evacuates-troops-guarding-tomb-inside-Syria-PM.html|title=Turkish troops enter Syria to relocate historic tomb|work=Mail Online|location=London|date=22 February 2015|access-date=22 February 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150222173830/http://www.dailymail.co.uk/wires/afp/article-2963690/Turkey-evacuates-troops-guarding-tomb-inside-Syria-PM.html|archive-date=22 February 2015|url-status=live}}</ref> Later, in two incidents in July and September, two soldiers were killed and five wounded by cross-border fire from ISIL territory in Syria.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/07/24/world/europe/turkey-isis-us-airstrikes-syria.html|title=U.S. Jets to Use Turkish Bases in War on ISIS|date=24 July 2015|work=The New York Times|accessdate=12 April 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160708164824/http://www.nytimes.com/2015/07/24/world/europe/turkey-isis-us-airstrikes-syria.html|archive-date=8 July 2016|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2015/09/01/Turkish-soldier-killed-in-cross-border-fire-from-ISIS-territory-in-Syria-.html|title=Turkish soldier killed in cross-border fire from ISIS territory in Syria|publisher=|access-date=2016-02-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190331181500/https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2015/09/01/Turkish-soldier-killed-in-cross-border-fire-from-ISIS-territory-in-Syria-.html|archive-date=2019-03-31|url-status=live}}</ref> On 15 February 2016, a soldier died at the border during clashes against human smugglers that tried to cross the border illegally.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hurriyetdailynews.com/turkish-soldier-killed-in-intervention-against-human-smugglers-at-syrian-border.aspx?pageID=238&nID=95187&NewsCatID=352|title=Turkish soldier killed in intervention against human smugglers at Syrian border - MIDEAST|publisher=|accessdate=12 April 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160302123604/http://www.hurriyetdailynews.com/turkish-soldier-killed-in-intervention-against-human-smugglers-at-syrian-border.aspx?pageID=238&nID=95187&NewsCatID=352|archive-date=2 March 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> Two Turkish soldiers died in a suicide bombing at a Syrian border crossing in mid-August.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-syria-turkey-idUSKCN10P0SE|title=Islamic State says bus blast killed 50 fighters at Syria-Turkey crossing|date=15 August 2017|publisher=|accessdate=1 April 2017|via=Reuters|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170307185531/http://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-syria-turkey-idUSKCN10P0SE|archive-date=7 March 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nFollowing the start of [[Operation Euphrates Shield|Turkey's ground incursion into Syria]] against ISIL and Kurdish forces in late August 2016, 72 soldiers had died by 29 March 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.haberler.com/firat-kalkani-nda-sehit-olan-72-askerin-anisina-10477562-haberi/|title=F\u0131rat Kalkan\u0131'nda \u015eehit Olan 72 Askerin An\u0131s\u0131na, Afrin'e 72 U\u00e7akla Sald\u0131r\u0131 D\u00fczenlendi}}</ref> 61\u201396 more died as result of Turkey's [[Operation Olive Branch|second large incursion]] between 2018 and 2019,<ref>54 killed (20 Jan.\u20136 July 2018),[https://www.aa.com.tr/en/turkey/turkey-neutralizes-over-4-500-terrorists-in-afrin-army/1196627] 1 killed (13 Dec. 2018),[https://www.france24.com/en/20181213-syria-afrin-turkish-soldier-killed-kurdish-militia-ypg] 1 killed (18 Feb. 2019),[https://www.dailysabah.com/war-on-terror/2019/02/18/1-turkish-soldier-killed-during-anti-terror-op-in-northern-syria/amp] 1 killed (31 March 2019),[https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-syria-turkey/one-turkish-soldier-killed-in-syria-military-retaliates-ministry-idUSKCN1RC0HR] 1 killed (4 May 2019),[https://www.hurriyetdailynews.co