n Idlib Governorate do not include unconfirmed claims of 50\u2013100 dead in the February 2020 [[2020 Balyun airstrikes|Balyun airstrikes]].[https://www.spiegel.de/politik/ausland/idlib-tuerkische-soldaten-sterben-durch-luftangriffe-in-syrien-a-f42bf8b4-e061-4a7c-a697-7fc97fe37c3a][https://www.al-monitor.com/pulse/originals/2020/02/turkey-syria-russia-deciphering-attack-on-turkish-troops.html][https://www.msn.com/en-us/news/world/dozens-of-turkish-soldiers-killed-in-strike-in-idlib-in-syria/ar-BB10uvmc?li=BBnb7Kz][https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2020/mar/02/erdogan-turkey-syria-assad?] Instead, they include 33 soldiers killed in the airstrike confirmed by Turkey.[https://www.reuters.com/article/us-syria-security-turkey-military-attack/attack-in-syrias-idlib-killed-33-turkish-soldiers-hatay-governor-idUSKCN20M030]</ref> One soldier also died in March 2019, in the area of Operation Euphrates Shield.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.dailysabah.com/war-on-terror/2019/03/15/turkish-soldier-killed-during-operations-in-northern-syria |title=Turkish soldier killed during operations in northern Syria |access-date=2019-04-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190408124825/https://www.dailysabah.com/war-on-terror/2019/03/15/turkish-soldier-killed-during-operations-in-northern-syria |archive-date=2019-04-08 |url-status=live }}</ref> Another 16 Turkish soldiers died during [[2019 Turkish offensive into north-eastern Syria|Turkey's third incursion]] in clashes against the SDF.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aa.com.tr/tr/baris-pinari-harekati/bakan-akar-yasaklanan-hicbir-muhimmati-veya-kimyasal-silahi-kullanmadik/1651521|title=Bakan Akar: Yasaklanan hi\u00e7bir m\u00fchimmat\u0131 veya kimyasal silah\u0131 kullanmad\u0131k|website=aa.com.tr}}<br />[http://www.hurriyetdailynews.com/turkish-soldier-killed-by-accident-in-n-syria-149072 Turkish soldier killed by accident in N Syria]<br />[https://www.dailysabah.com/war-on-terror/2019/11/28/2-soldiers-killed-in-ypg-attack-in-se-turkey 2 soldiers killed in YPG attack in SE Turkey]<br />[https://www.aa.com.tr/en/middle-east/2-turkish-soldiers-martyred-in-terrorist-attacks/1661823 2 Turkish soldiers martyred in terrorist attacks]</ref> During January 2020, between seven and ten Turkish soldiers were killed in two car bombings near [[Ras al-Ayn]] and in northern Raqqa,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.arabnews.com/node/1610276/middle-east|title=Four Turkish soldiers killed in car bombing in Syria|website=Arab News|date=8 January 2020}}</ref><ref>[http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=152556 Ras Al-Ain bomb attacks cause the highest daily death toll ever among Turkish soldiers]</ref><ref>[http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=153093 Three Turkish soldiers among ten killed in car-bomb explosion north of Raqqa]</ref> while one or four more died in two bombings near Ras al-Ayn in March.<ref>[https://ahvalnews.com/ras-al-ayn/turkish-soldier-three-locals-killed-ras-al-ayn-bombing Turkish soldier, three locals killed in Ras al Ayn bombing]<br>[http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=157185 Four explosions hit areas in Ras al-Ain countryside leaves eight people dead, including Turkish soldiers]</ref> One soldier was also killed in an accident in the area of Operation Peace Spring in February 2020,<ref>[https://www.hurriyet.com.tr/gundem/suriyede-kazada-sehit-olan-uzman-onbasi-ceyhun-tas-memleketine-ugurlandi-41443140 Suriye\u2019de kazada \u015fehit olan Uzman Onba\u015f\u0131 Ceyhun Ta\u015f, memleketine u\u011furland\u0131]</ref> and one committed suicide in the area in March 2020.<ref>[https://hawarnews.com/en/haber/for-refusing-to-stay-in-serkaniy-turkish-soldier-committed-suicide-h15491.html For refusing to stay in Ser\u00eakaniy\u00ea, Turkish soldier committed suicide]</ref>\n\n{{flagicon|France}} '''1 serviceman killed''' <br /> The [[\u00c9lys\u00e9e Palace]] announced in September 2017 that a French servicemen of the 13th regiment of paratroopers died in the Levant region during Operation Chammal. It was not known where the precise location of the soldier's death.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.france24.com/en/20170923-french-soldier-killed-iraq-syria-military-zone|title=French soldier killed in Iraq-Syria military zone, \u00c9lys\u00e9e Palace says|date=23 September 2017|website=France 24|accessdate=19 February 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190224175919/https://www.france24.com/en/20170923-french-soldier-killed-iraq-syria-military-zone|archive-date=24 February 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n{{flagicon|United Kingdom}} '''1 serviceman killed''' <br />A British soldier, named as Sgt Matt Tunroe of the 3rd Battalion the Parachute Regiment died on 30 March 2018 in [[Manbij|Manbij.]] This was initially reported as an IED explosion from which a U.S. soldier had also been killed from.<ref name=\"cnn.com\">{{cite web|title=US and British troops killed in Syria blast|url=https://www.cnn.com/2018/03/30/politics/syria-coalition-ied/index.html|access-date=2018-04-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180331104211/https://www.cnn.com/2018/03/30/politics/syria-coalition-ied/index.html|archive-date=2018-03-31|url-status=live}}</ref> However, the Ministry of Defence later clarified it was a case of [[friendly fire]], caused by the accidental detonation of explosives carried by another coalition soldier.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.itv.com/news/2019-07-27/british-soldier-sergeant-matt-tonroe-killed-by-friendly-fire-not-roadside-bomb-investigation-finds/|title=British soldier Sergeant Matt Tonroe killed by friendly fire not roadside bomb, investigation finds|website=ITV News|language=en|access-date=2020-01-08}}</ref>\n\n{{flagicon|United States}} '''9 servicemen killed'''<br /> A U.S. pilot was killed on 30 November 2014, when his [[General Dynamics F-16 Fighting Falcon|F-16]] fighter aircraft crashed in Jordan following a combat mission against the Islamic State jihadist group.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.f-16.net/f-16-news-article4910.html|title=Pilot killed as U.S. F-16 crashes in Jordan|publisher=|access-date=2018-07-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180707230817/http://www.f-16.net/f-16-news-article4910.html|archive-date=2018-07-07|url-status=live}}</ref> Also, a U.S. special forces member died due to a bomb explosion while supporting Kurdish-led forces during the ''[[Raqqa campaign (2016\u20132017)|Wrath of Euphrates]]'' offensive against ISIL-held [[Raqqa]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2016/11/25/US-service-member-killed-in-blast-in-Syria-.html|title=US service member killed in blast in Syria|publisher=|access-date=2016-11-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180710040931/http://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2016/11/25/US-service-member-killed-in-blast-in-Syria-.html|archive-date=2018-07-10|url-status=live}}</ref> Two other service members died due to non-combat causes in northern Syria in 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://abcnews.go.com/International/us-service-member-killed-accident-syria/story?id=47658836|title=US service member killed in Syria identified as 22-year-old from Georgia|first=A. B. C.|last=News|date=27 May 2017|website=ABC News|access-date=26 May 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170526140904/http://abcnews.go.com/International/us-service-member-killed-accident-syria/story?id=47658836|archive-date=26 May 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> A US servicemen died on 30 March 2018 by an IED explosion in Manbij.<ref name=\"cnn.com\"/> Four Americans, including two soldiers, were killed by a bombing in Manbij city on 16 January 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://abcnews.go.com/Politics/american-service-members-killed-bomb-blast-northern-syria/story?id=60444620|title=3 of the Americans killed in bomb blast in northern Syria identified|website=ABC News|accessdate=19 February 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190220232117/https://abcnews.go.com/Politics/american-service-members-killed-bomb-blast-northern-syria/story?id=60444620|archive-date=20 February 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2019/01/16/politics/syria-attack-us-patrolled-city/index.html|title=4 Americans killed in Syria attack. ISIS claims responsibility|author1=Zachary Cohen|author2=Veronica Stracqualursi|author3=Kevin Liptak|website=CNN|accessdate=19 February 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416172831/https://www.cnn.com/2019/01/16/politics/syria-attack-us-patrolled-city/index.html|archive-date=16 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> One American soldier was killed on 28 April 2019,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.wxyz.com/news/army-private-from-southwest-detroit-dies-in-syria-in-non-combat-incident |title=Army private from southwest Detroit dies in Syria in non-combat incident |access-date=2019-05-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190506131337/https://www.wxyz.com/news/army-private-from-southwest-detroit-dies-in-syria-in-non-combat-incident |archive-date=2019-05-06 |url-status=live }}</ref> possibly due to Turkish shelling.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=126569 |title=Mystery surrounds the killing of a US soldier in the countryside of Ayn al-Arab (Kobani) amid accusations against Turkey of targeting him |access-date=2019-05-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190505164800/http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=126569 |archive-date=2019-05-05 |url-status=live }}</ref> Another US soldier died in Syria on January 24, 2020, following a rollover crash in Deir ez-Zor province.<ref>[https://www.washingtontimes.com/news/2020/jan/25/army-identifies-antonio-moore-soldier-killed-syria/ Army identifies U.S. soldier killed in Syria]</ref>\n\n==Foreign air-strike casualties==\nThe SOHR considers the following figures on ISIL, al-Nusra and other rebel fatalities to be higher due to the groups' efforts to hide their losses.\n\n===[[American-led intervention in the Syrian Civil War|American-led intervention]]===\n\nAccording to SOHR, U.S.-led Coalition airstrikes have killed 14,024 people across Syria, of which: 9,170 dead were ISIL fighters, 360 Al-Nusra Front militants and other rebels, 169 government soldiers and 3,835 civilians. The air strikes occurred in the period between 23 September 2014 and 15 March 2020.<ref name=SOHR/>\n\n===[[Russian military intervention in the Syrian Civil War|Russian intervention]]===\nAccording to SOHR, Russian airstrikes in Syria killed about 20,000 people, of whom 5,244 were ISIL fighters, 6,128 militants from the Al-Qaeda affiliate al-Nusra Front and other rebel forces, 8,649 civilians and five Turkish soldiers. The air strikes occurred in the period between 30 September 2015 and 31 March 2020.<ref name=\"russianair\">{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/?p=371683|title=\u0639\u0644\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0631\u063a\u0645 \u0645\u0646 \u0648\u0642\u0641 \u0625\u0637\u0644\u0627\u0642 \u0627\u0644\u0646\u0627\u0631 \u0627\u0644\u0645\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0635\u0644 \u0645\u0646\u0630 26 \u064a\u0648\u0645\u0627\u064b.. \u0627\u0633\u062a\u0634\u0647\u0627\u062f 27 \u0645\u062f\u0646\u064a\u0627\u064b \u0628\u0636\u0631\u0628\u0627\u062a \u062c\u0648\u064a\u0629 \u0631\u0648\u0633\u064a\u0629 \u062e\u0644\u0627\u0644 \u0634\u0647\u0631 \u0622\u0630\u0627\u0631/\u0645\u0627\u0631\u0633 2020|work=SOHR|date=March 31, 2020|accessdate=March 31, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.smh.com.au/world/russian-bombing-mistake-kills-three-turkish-soldiers-in-syria-20170210-gu9r5d.html |title=Russian bombing mistake kills three Turkish soldiers in Syria |access-date=2019-06-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190601102458/https://www.smh.com.au/world/russian-bombing-mistake-kills-three-turkish-soldiers-in-syria-20170210-gu9r5d.html |archive-date=2019-06-01 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=155503&__cf_chl_jschl_tk__=7c46b3e6934bc2dd742fc1e8b62bb0d57d8e6ed5-1582320782-0-AXfGWJ7C7W4IxU3BKbjbv0dI3GVmnpucDOvRwlH5V4Z35UNFweIYYoZZODH8x-Xj3-X621fDvEUfBC64mD3-lap0fcnSW6f_IljyF4iL2vRtVbjAqJxdIGXv0ZLSgLVzlaqrXTN66dVe-Wyzv76FHxd6K6ldPaH971bwee_NxnCLWF-l6o2uInxUbGCbN8x2CBu_7aKxijk_mrcFZMkCrhFQKGcCzB-uw8zD2xjgH_GeSqVl3LWIABnAtbj236qdYqUpQeSe9afK9n0q_YzqqxnwyjETov0RQ7lT4pD90DT7</ref> The ''New York Times'' accused the Russian air force of specifically focusing on attacking civilian hospitals and other medical facilities, including hospitals on so-called \"deconfliction list\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/10/13/world/middleeast/russia-bombing-syrian-hospitals.html|title=12 Hours. 4 Syrian Hospitals Bombed. One Culprit: Russia.|last=Hill|first=Evan|date=2019-10-13|work=The New York Times|access-date=2019-10-13|last2=Triebert|first2=Christiaan|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191013071012/https://www.nytimes.com/2019/10/13/world/middleeast/russia-bombing-syrian-hospitals.html|archive-date=2019-10-13|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nAccording to Airwars, a not-for-profit transparency project aimed both at tracking and archiving international military actions in conflict zones such as Iraq, Syria and Libya, Russian airstrikes have killed 3,736\u20135,510 civilians <ref>{{cite web|url=https://airwars.org/conflict/russian-military-in-syria/|title=Reported civilian deaths from Russian military strikes in Syria|access-date=2019-10-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190524182735/https://airwars.org/conflict/russian-military-in-syria/|archive-date=2019-05-24|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://airwars.org/about/team/|title=Airwars: About Us|access-date=2019-10-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190426235526/https://airwars.org/about/team/|archive-date=2019-04-26|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nAccording to the Russian Defense Ministry, since the start of Russia's aerial campaign in Syria and by 20 October 2018, the Russian Air Force killed more than 87,500 rebels and ISIL fighters.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.timeslive.co.za/news/world/2018-10-20-russia-says-88000-syria-rebels-killed/|title=Russia says 88,000 Syria rebels killed|first=|last=TimesLIVE|publisher=|accessdate=20 October 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181020113627/https://www.timeslive.co.za/news/world/2018-10-20-russia-says-88000-syria-rebels-killed/|archive-date=20 October 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Medical workers killed==\n{{Pie chart \n | caption=Killings of medical workers since the start of the Syrian Civil War, according to a [[Physicians for Human Rights|PHR]] summary<ref name=\"Medical_stats\">{{cite report |url= https://s3.amazonaws.com/PHR_Reports/doctors-in-the-crosshairs.pdf |last1= Baker |first1= Elise |last2= Brown |first2= Widney |title= Doctors in the Crosshairs: Four Years of Attacks on Health Care in Syria |publisher= Physicians for Human Rights |date= March 2015 |accessdate= 13 March 2015 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20150317193410/https://s3.amazonaws.com/PHR_Reports/doctors-in-the-crosshairs.pdf |archivedate= 17 March 2015 |url-status= live }}</ref>\n | other = \n | label1 = Attacks by government forces\n | value1 = 95.5 | color1 = Red\n | label2 = ISIL or rebel groups\n | value2 = 2.5 | color2 = Grey\n | label3 = Kurdish forces\n | value3 = 0.1 | color3 = Blue\n | label4 = Unknown forces\n | value4 = 1.9 | color4 = Black\n }}\n\nA February 2015 joint report by the Center for Public Health and Human Rights of the Johns Hopkins Bloomberg School of Public Health and the Syrian American Medical Society asserted that \"Syria is the most dangerous place in the world to be a doctor\".<ref>{{Cite report |author=  |authorlink=  |date= February 2015 |title= Syrian Medical Voices from the Ground: The Ordeal of Syria\u2019s Healthcare Professionals |url= http://media.nbcbayarea.com/documents/Syrian+Medical+Voices+from+the+Ground.pdf |publisher= The Center for Public Health and Human Rights of the Johns Hopkins Bloomberg School of Public Health and the Syrian American Medical Society |page=  |docket=  |asin=  |accessdate= 13 March 2015 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20150402115606/http://media.nbcbayarea.com/documents/Syrian+Medical+Voices+from+the+Ground.pdf |archivedate= 2 April 2015 |url-status= live }}</ref> Roughly half (an estimated 15,000)<ref name=JapanTimes_March2015/> of Syrian doctors fled the country.<ref>{{cite news |url= http://www.nbcchicago.com/news/local/Chicago-Doctors-Syrian-War-Hospital-295954681.html |title= Chicago Doctors Risk Arrest, Torture to Aid Dire Medical Care Void in Syria |last1= Leitner |first1= Tammy |last2= Capitanini |first2= Lisa |publisher= NBC Chicago |date= 12 April 2015 |accessdate= 13 March 2015 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20150402150834/http://www.nbcchicago.com/news/local/Chicago-Doctors-Syrian-War-Hospital-295954681.html |archive-date= 2 April 2015 |url-status= live }}</ref> The government passed a law in 2012 making it illegal to render medical aid to anyone suspected to be an opposition member and [[Amnesty International]] found that doctors and medical staff also took part in [[torture]] of patients.<ref name=JapanTimes_March2015/>\n\n[[Physicians for Human Rights]] has been tracking the medical personnel deaths in Syria, though they state that \"these numbers are conservative given the difficulties in reporting during a war.\" As of the end of September 2015, the number of medical workers killed in the Syrian civil war totaled 679.<ref>{{cite web|title=Anatomy of A Crisis: A Map of Attack on Health Care in Syria|url=https://s3.amazonaws.com/PHR_syria_map/web/index.html|website=Physicians for Human Rights|accessdate=23 October 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151031030344/https://s3.amazonaws.com/PHR_syria_map/web/index.html|archive-date=31 October 2015|url-status=live}}</ref> In March 2017, the number of killed medical personnel was updated to more than 800. 723 of these deaths were attributable to the Syrian government, while 72 were killed by ISIL or rebel groups, one by Kurdish forces, and 13 by unidentified forces.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/wires/afp/article-4314462/Over-800-health-workers-killed-Syrian-war-crimes-report.html|title=Over 800 health workers killed in Syrian 'war crimes': report|work=AFP|accessdate=14 March 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170315181901/http://www.dailymail.co.uk/wires/afp/article-4314462/Over-800-health-workers-killed-Syrian-war-crimes-report.html|archive-date=15 March 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n[[M\u00e9decins Sans Fronti\u00e8res]] has reported that suppliers in Syria refuse to sell essential medical supplies such as gauze and surgical threads to doctors due to government intimidation, with this being a particular problem for besieged areas.<ref name=\"JapanTimes_March2015\">{{cite web | url= http://www.japantimes.co.jp/opinion/2015/03/20/commentary/world-commentary/doctors-being-targeted-in-syrias-brutal-war/#.VQwwHiPFLqD | last= Chelala | first= Cesar | title= Doctors being targeted in Syria\u2019s brutal war | publisher= The Japan Times | date= 20 March 2015 | accessdate= 20 March 2015 | archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20150323213613/http://www.japantimes.co.jp/opinion/2015/03/20/commentary/world-commentary/doctors-being-targeted-in-syrias-brutal-war#.VQwwHiPFLqD | archive-date= 23 March 2015 | url-status= live }}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Casualties of the Iraq War]]\n*[[Casualty recording]]\n{{Portal|Asia|War}}\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|group=note}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n{{Syrian civil war}}\n\n[[Category:War casualties by war]]\n[[Category:Syrian Civil War]]\n", "text_old": "{{Short description|deaths and injuries from the war}}\n{{Human toll of Syrian Civil War}}\n[[File:Aleppo hospital.PNG|thumb|Doctors and medical staff treating injured rebel fighters and civilians in Aleppo]]\nEstimates of the total number of '''deaths in the [[Syrian Civil War]]''', by opposition activist groups, vary between 384,000 and about 586,100 as of March 2020.<ref name=SOHR>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=157193|title=Syrian Revolution .. nine years on: 586,100 persons killed and millions of Syrians displaced and injured|last=|first=|date=14 March 2020|website=|publisher=SOHR}}</ref> On 23 April 2016, the [[Staffan de Mistura|United Nations and Arab League Envoy to Syria]] put out an estimate of 400,000 that had died in the war.<ref name=UN1>{{cite web|url=http://www.aljazeera.com/news/2016/04/staffan-de-mistura-400000-killed-syria-civil-war-160423055735629.html|title=Syria death toll: UN envoy estimates 400,000 killed|publisher=Al Jazeera|accessdate=23 April 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160424031035/http://www.aljazeera.com/news/2016/04/staffan-de-mistura-400000-killed-syria-civil-war-160423055735629.html|archive-date=24 April 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> Based on Syria's pre-war [[Demographics of Syria|population]] of 20.8 million from 2011,<ref name=\"Khalifa2013\">{{citation|last=Khalifa|first=Mustafa|title=The impossible partition of Syria|url=http://www.arab-reform.net/en/node/510|pages=3\u20135|year=2013|publisher=[[Arab Reform Initiative]]|quote='''Arabs''' constitute the major ethnic group in Syria, making up between 80 and 85% of the population. <br/> '''Kurds''' are the second largest ethnic group in Syria, making up around 10% of the Syrian population and distributed among four regions...with a Yazidi minority that numbers around 40,000...<br/>'''Turkmen''' are the third largest ethnic group in Syria, making up around 4\u20135% of the population. Some estimations indicate that they are the second biggest group, outnumbering Kurds, drawing on the fact that Turkmen are divided into two groups: the rural Turkmen who make up 30% of the Turkmen in Syria and who have kept their mother tongue, and the urban Turkmen who have become Arabised and no longer speak their mother language... <br/> '''Assyrians''' are the fourth largest ethnic group in Syria. They represent the original and oldest inhabitants of Syria, today making up around 3\u20134% of the Syrian population... <br/> '''Circassians''' are the fifth largest ethnic group in Syria, making up around 1.5% of the population... <br/> '''Armenians''' are sixth largest ethnic group in Syria, making up around 1% of the population... <br/> There are also a small number of other ethnic groups in Syria, including Greeks, Persians, Albanians, Bosnian, Pashtuns, Russians and Azeri people...|access-date=2019-03-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161009155010/http://www.arab-reform.net/en/node/510|archive-date=2016-10-09|url-status=live}}</ref> this represented approximately {{Percentage|400,000|20,800,000}} of Syria's pre-war population.\n\n[[UNICEF]] reported that over 500 children had been killed by early February 2012.<ref>{{cite news |agency=Agence France-Presse |url=https://www.google.com/hostednews/afp/article/ALeqM5jn_Hwm1c4s57hZroY2XO3gtvHl_g?docId=CNG.d4e0242216423f0ddcaa53de60d07900.f1 |title=UNICEF says 400 children killed in Syria unrest |work=Google News |date=7 February 2012 |accessdate=22 February 2012 |location=Geneva |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120525033139/http://www.google.com/hostednews/afp/article/ALeqM5jn_Hwm1c4s57hZroY2XO3gtvHl_g?docId=CNG.d4e0242216423f0ddcaa53de60d07900.f1 |archive-date=25 May 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.upi.com/Top_News/Special/2012/03/23/UNICEF-500-children-died-in-Syrian-war/UPI-69191332522535/ |title=UNICEF: 500 children died in Syrian war |publisher=UPI.com |date=23 March 2012 |accessdate=6 July 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120327093556/http://www.upi.com/Top_News/Special/2012/03/23/UNICEF-500-children-died-in-Syrian-war/UPI-69191332522535/ |archive-date=27 March 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> Another 400 children were reportedly arrested and tortured in Syrian prisons.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.couriermail.com.au/news/breaking-news/unicef-says-400-children-killed-in-syria/story-e6freonf-1226265280318 |title=UNICEF says 400 children killed in Syria |work=The Courier-Mail |date=8 February 2012 |accessdate=16 February 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130514041232/http://www.couriermail.com.au/news/breaking-news/unicef-says-400-children-killed-in-syria/story-e6freonf-1226265280318 |archive-date=14 May 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Peralta |first=Eyder |url=https://www.npr.org/blogs/thetwo-way/2012/02/03/146346490/rights-group-says-syrian-security-forces-detained-tortured-children |title=Rights Group Says Syrian Security Forces Detained, Tortured Children: The Two-Way |work=NPR |date=3 February 2012 |accessdate=16 February 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150427232713/http://www.npr.org/blogs/thetwo-way/2012/02/03/146346490/rights-group-says-syrian-security-forces-detained-tortured-children |archive-date=27 April 2015 |url-status=live }}</ref> Both claims were contested by the Syrian government.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sana.sy/eng/22/2012/02/14/400319.htm|title=Al-Jafari: Syria has Right to Protect its Citizen, Combat Terrorism and Armed Violence|work=Syrian Arab news agency|date=14 February 2012|accessdate=10 April 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120319005802/http://sana.sy/eng/22/2012/02/14/400319.htm|archivedate=19 March 2012}}</ref> The United Nations stated that by the end of April 2014, 8,803 children had been killed,<ref name=UN>{{cite news |url=http://edition.cnn.com/2014/08/22/world/meast/syria-conflict/index.html?hpt=imi_c2 |title=With more than 191,000 dead in Syria, U.N. rights chief slams global 'paralysis' |work=CNN |access-date=2014-08-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150411102510/http://edition.cnn.com/2014/08/22/world/meast/syria-conflict/index.html?hpt=imi_c2 |archive-date=2015-04-11 |url-status=live }}</ref> while the Oxford Research Group said that a total of 11,420 children died in the conflict by late November 2013.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/middle-east/bombs-and-guns-have-killed-11500-children-in-syria-research-shows-including-some-executed-and-tortured-8960809.html|title=Bombs and guns \u2018have killed 11,500 children\u2019 in Syria, research shows, including some executed and tortured|work=The Independent|accessdate=25 October 2014|location=London|first=Sophie|last=Robehmed|date=24 November 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141029123604/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/middle-east/bombs-and-guns-have-killed-11500-children-in-syria-research-shows-including-some-executed-and-tortured-8960809.html|archive-date=29 October 2014|url-status=live}}</ref> By mid-March 2020, the opposition activist group [[Syrian Observatory for Human Rights]] (SOHR) reported the number of children killed in the conflict had risen to 22,075, while at the same time 13,704 women were also killed.<ref name=SOHR/>\n\nAdditionally, over 600 detainees and political prisoners had died under torture by the start of 2012.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2012/01/06/world/middleeast/hundreds-tortured-in-syria-human-rights-group-says.html |work=The New York Times |first=Kareem |last=Fahim |title=Hundreds Tortured in Syria, Human Rights Group Says |date=5 January 2012 |access-date=26 February 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130513032839/http://www.nytimes.com/2012/01/06/world/middleeast/hundreds-tortured-in-syria-human-rights-group-says.html |archive-date=13 May 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref> By February 2017, [[Amnesty International]] estimated between 5,000 and 13,000 people had been executed in government prisons, and thousands more people are reported to have died due to torture by Syrian authorities.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dw.com/en/ai-estimates-up-to-13000-civilians-executed-in-syrian-military-prison-over-four-years/a-37435537|title=AI estimates up to 13,000 civilians executed in Syrian military prison over four years - News - DW - 07.02.2017|first=Deutsche Welle|last=(www.dw.com)|website=DW.COM|access-date=2017-04-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170430025758/http://www.dw.com/en/ai-estimates-up-to-13000-civilians-executed-in-syrian-military-prison-over-four-years/a-37435537|archive-date=2017-04-30|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Overall deaths==\n[[File:Total deaths during the syrian civil war (October 2013).png|thumb|right|275px|Total deaths over the course of the conflict in Syria (18 March 2011 \u2013 18 October 2013)]]\n[[File:Deaths per week during the syrian civil war (October 2013).png|thumb|right|275px|Weekly deaths over the course of the conflict in Syria (18 March 2011 \u2013 18 October 2013)]]\nAll of the following totals include civilians, rebels and government forces:\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Source\n! Casualties\n! Time period\n|-\n|Syrian Centre for Policy Research\n|'''470,000''' killed<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pbs.org/wgbh/frontline/article/a-staggering-new-death-toll-for-syrias-war-470000/|title=A Staggering New Death Toll for Syria\u2019s War \u2014 470,000|last=|first=|date=28 May 2016|website=|publisher=|access-date=25 August 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170820232300/http://www.pbs.org/wgbh/frontline/article/a-staggering-new-death-toll-for-syrias-war-470000|archive-date=20 August 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|15 March 2011 \u2013 11 February 2016\n|-\n|[[Staffan de Mistura|UN and Arab League Envoy to Syria]]\n|'''400,000''' killed<ref name=UN1/>\n|15 March 2011 \u2013 23 April 2016\n|-\n|[[Syrian Observatory for Human Rights]]\n|'''384,000\u2013586,100''' killed<ref name=SOHR/>\n|15 March 2011 \u2013 14 March 2020\n|-\n|}\n\nAt the start of the war, Al Jazeera journalist [[Nir Rosen]] stated that many of the deaths reported daily by activists were in fact armed insurgents falsely presented as civilian deaths, but said that real civilian deaths do occur on a regular basis.<ref name=nirrosen>{{cite news|url=http://www.aljazeera.com/indepth/features/2012/02/201221315020166516.html|title=Q&A: Nir Rosen on Syria's armed opposition|work=Al Jazeera|date=21 February 2012|first=Nir|last=Rosen|accessdate=22 February 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120222030014/http://www.aljazeera.com/indepth/features/2012/02/201221315020166516.html|archive-date=22 February 2012|url-status=live}}</ref> Several Middle East analysts, including Sharmine Narwani from the Lebanese [[Al Akhbar (Lebanon)|Al Akhbar]] newspaper and the UAE/Saudi [[Al Arabiya]] website, also urged caution.<ref name=\"Narwani 28Feb2012\">{{cite news|last=Narwani|first=Sharmine|url=http://english.al-akhbar.com/content/questioning-syrian-%E2%80%9Ccasualty-list%E2%80%9D|title=Questioning the Syrian \"Casualty List\"|date=28 February 2012|work=Al-Akhbar|accessdate=17 March 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151124102050/http://english.al-akhbar.com/content/questioning-syrian-%E2%80%9Ccasualty-list%E2%80%9D|archive-date=24 November 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://english.alarabiya.net/articles/2012/03/25/203106.html |title=Eman El-Shenawi: Raising a brow at the Syrian death toll |work=Al Arabiya |date=25 March 2012 |accessdate=10 April 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120331184420/http://english.alarabiya.net/articles/2012/03/25/203106.html |archive-date=31 March 2012 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rt.com/news/syria-observers-civilians-insurgents-707/ |title=Observers in Syria: Time to separate civilians from insurgents? |publisher=Rt.com |date= |accessdate=8 July 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190610214220/https://www.rt.com/news/syria-observers-civilians-insurgents-707/ |archive-date=10 June 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nThis was later confirmed when in late May 2012, Rami Abdulrahman of the [[Syrian Observatory for Human Rights]], which is one of the opposition-affiliated groups counting the number of those killed in the uprising, stated that civilians who had taken up arms during the earliest days of the conflict were being counted under the category of \"civilians\" as they were not army nor army defectors.<ref name=morethan13000>{{cite news|url=http://gulfnews.com/news/mena/syria/more-than-13-000-killed-in-syria-since-march-2011-ngo-1.1028367|title=More than 13,000 killed in Syria since March 2011: NGO|agency=Agence France-Presse|date=27 May 2012|accessdate=27 May 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160722135003/http://gulfnews.com/news/mena/syria/more-than-13-000-killed-in-syria-since-march-2011-ngo-1.1028367|archive-date=22 July 2016|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"violence\">{{cite web |author=Agence France Presse |url=http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/global-filipino/world/06/10/12/syria-violence-kills-12-revolt-toll-tops-14100 |title=Syria violence kills 12 as revolt toll tops 14,100 |publisher=Abs-cbnnews.com |date= |accessdate=8 July 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120702001616/http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/global-filipino/world/06/10/12/syria-violence-kills-12-revolt-toll-tops-14100 |archive-date=2 July 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=over14400>{{cite web |url=http://www.thesundaily.my/news/408099 |title=Over 14,400 killed in 15-month Syria revolt |publisher=Thesundaily.my |date= |accessdate=8 July 2012 }}{{dead link|date=August 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\nIn May 2013, SOHR stated that at least 41,000 of those killed during the conflict were [[Alawites]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/05/14/syria-death-toll-120000_n_3272610.html |title=Syria Death Toll Likely As High As 120,000, Group Says |publisher=Huffingtonpost.com |date=2013-05-14 |accessdate=2013-08-30 |first=Eline |last=Gordts |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131115032827/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/05/14/syria-death-toll-120000_n_3272610.html |archive-date=2013-11-15 |url-status=live }}</ref> By April 2015, reportedly a third of the country's 250,000 Alawites that were of fighting age had been killed.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/middleeast/syria/11518232/In-Syrias-war-Alawites-pay-heavy-price-for-loyalty-to-Bashar-al-Assad.html|title=In Syria's war, Alawites pay heavy price for loyalty to Bashar al-Assad|date=7 April 2015|work=Telegraph.co.uk|location=London|first=Ruth|last=Sherlock|access-date=5 April 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150407102223/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/middleeast/syria/11518232/In-Syrias-war-Alawites-pay-heavy-price-for-loyalty-to-Bashar-al-Assad.html|archive-date=7 April 2015|url-status=live}}</ref> In April 2017, a pro-opposition source claimed 150,000 young Alawites had died.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.middleeastmonitor.com/20170420-150000-alawites-killed-in-6-year-syria-war/|title=150,000 Alawites killed in 6-year Syria war|date=20 April 2017|publisher=|access-date=21 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190921035500/https://www.middleeastmonitor.com/20170420-150000-alawites-killed-in-6-year-syria-war/|archive-date=21 September 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Death tolls by time periods===\nThe following figures were all compiled by the SOHR which is considered an authoritative source on the matter.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mcclatchydc.com/news/nation-world/world/middle-east/article24749608.html|title=Assad backers reportedly make up 43 percent of dead in Syria|work=mcclatchydc|accessdate=28 October 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151109132933/http://www.mcclatchydc.com/news/nation-world/world/middle-east/article24749608.html|archive-date=2015-11-09|url-status=dead}}</ref> The figures are only for documented deaths, while the SOHR estimates another 202,100 undocumented deaths had occurred.<ref name=SOHR/>\n[[File:Fatalities in the Syrian civil war (SOHR).png|thumb|right|275px|Monthly documented fatalities in the [[Syrian civil war]] according to [[SOHR]]:{{legend|lightblue|Civilians}}{{legend|Orange|Pro-government forces}}\n{{legend|#cae7c4|[[Syrian opposition|Syrian anti-government fighters]], [[People's Protection Units|YPG]]}}\n{{legend|Grey|[[Foreign rebel fighters in the Syrian Civil War|Foreign anti-government fighters]]}}\n]]\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Time Period\n! Pro-government forces\n! Anti-government forces\n! Civilians\n! Grand Total (inc. unidentified)\n|-\n|'''2011'''\n|'''3,138''' killed\n|'''619''' killed\n|'''3,968''' killed\n|'''7,841''' killed\n|-\n|'''2012'''\n|'''18,928''' killed\n|'''9,746''' killed\n|'''19,924''' killed\n|'''49,361''' killed\n|-\n|'''2013'''\n|'''30,269''' killed\n|'''18,914''' killed\n|'''22,806''' killed\n|'''73,929''' killed\n|-\n|'''2014'''\n|'''25,106''' killed\n|'''32,803''' killed\n|'''18,038''' killed\n|'''76,268''' killed\n|-\n|'''2015'''\n|'''17,668''' killed\n|'''23,601''' killed\n|'''13,021''' killed\n|'''54,574''' killed\n|-\n|'''2016'''\n|'''14,771''' killed\n|'''23,431''' killed\n|'''14,100''' killed\n|'''52,589''' killed\n|-\n|'''2017'''\n|'''10,771''' killed\n|'''14,064''' killed\n|'''13,369''' killed\n|'''34,700''' killed\n|-\n|'''2018'''\n|'''4,522''' killed\n|'''8,663''' killed\n|'''6,776''' killed\n|'''20,130''' killed\n|-\n|'''2019'''\n|'''2,968''' killed\n|'''4,727''' killed\n|'''3,488''' killed\n|'''11,244''' killed\n|-\n|'''''Total'''''\n|'''''128,141''''' killed\n|'''''134,477''''' killed\n|'''''115,490''''' killed\n|'''''380,636''''' killed<ref name=SOHR2>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=152189|title=Nearly 585,000 people have been killed since the beginning of the Syrian Revolution|last=|first=|date=4 January 2020|website=|publisher=SOHR}}</ref>\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Time Period\n! Pro-government forces\n! Anti-government forces\n! Civilians\n! Grand Total\n|-\n|'''January 2020'''\n|'''488''' killed\n|'''451''' killed\n|'''262''' killed\n|'''1,201''' killed<ref>[http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=154179 January 2020: Nearly 14,000 air and ground strikes, 13 massacres, and over 1,200 people killed]</ref>\n|-\n|'''February 2020'''\n|'''701''' killed\n|'''794''' killed\n|'''275''' killed\n|'''1,771''' killed<ref>[http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=156093 The highest death toll in 23 months: 1,771 persons killed across Syria in February 2020]</ref>\n|-\n|'''March 2020'''\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|'''''Total'''''\n|'''1,189''' killed\n|'''1,245''' killed\n|'''537''' killed\n|'''2,972''' killed\n|}\n\n===Death tolls by provinces===\nAccording to the Syrian opposition website ''Syrian Martyrs'', the conflict's death toll was 151,888 up to 30 April 2016, which was the time of its last update.<ref name=\"shuhadamain\">{{cite web|url=http://syrianshuhada.com/?lang=en&|title=Syrian Martyrs|publisher=Free Syria|accessdate=30 April 2016|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160404195534/http://www.syrianshuhada.com/?lang=en&|archivedate=4 April 2016}}</ref> The number includes 35,859 rebel combatants but does not include members of the government security forces or pro-government foreign combatants who have died.<ref name=\"Number as a civil / military\">{{cite web |url=http://syrianshuhada.com/?lang=en&a=st&st=7 |title=Number as a civil / military |publisher=Syrian Martyrs |accessdate=30 April 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304064949/http://syrianshuhada.com/?lang=en&a=st&st=7 |archive-date=4 March 2016 |url-status=live }}</ref> Early in the conflict, the ''Syrian Martyrs'' number of civilian deaths was significantly higher than the ones presented by other organisations, including the UN; among the reasons are that they recorded deaths even when no name is given for the reportedly killed individual and that they collated reports of deaths from more sources.<ref name=\"Syriancrisis\">{{cite news |last=Khera |first=Jastinder |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-middle-east-18093967 |title=Syria crisis: Counting the victims |publisher=Bbc.co.uk |date=29 May 2012 |accessdate=8 July 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120706234751/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-middle-east-18093967 |archive-date=6 July 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Governorate !! Number of deaths\n|-\n| [[Latakia Governorate|Latakia]] || 1,511\n|-\n| [[Rif Dimashq Governorate|Rif Dimashq]] || 34,813\n|-\n| [[Homs Governorate|Homs]] || 17,993\n|-\n| [[Hama Governorate|Hama]] || 9,867\n|-\n| [[Al-Hasakah Governorate|Al-Hasakah]] || 1,693\n|-\n| [[Daraa Governorate|Daraa]] || 14,227\n|-\n| [[Aleppo Governorate|Aleppo]] || 31,257\n|-\n| [[Deir ez-Zor Governorate|Deir ez-Zor]] || 9,696\n|-\n| [[Damascus Governorate|Damascus]] || 9,747\n|-\n| [[Tartus Governorate|Tartus]] || 555\n|-\n| [[Quneitra Governorate|Quneitra]] || 1,069\n|-\n| [[Idlib Governorate|Idlib]] || 16,699\n|-\n| [[As-Suwayda Governorate|As-Suwayda]] || 106\n|-\n| [[Raqqa Governorate|Raqqa]] || 2,655\n|-\t\n| Total || 151,888<ref name=\"shuhadamain\"/>\n|}\n\n==Civilian deaths==\n\nAccording to the pro-opposition [[Syrian Network for Human Rights]], 224,948 civilians had been killed between March 2011 and March 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sn4hr.org/blog/2018/09/24/civilian-death-toll//|title=Civilian Death Toll|first=Syrian Network For Human|last=Rights|date=24 September 2019|publisher=|accessdate=24 September 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191102013022/http://sn4hr.org/blog/2018/09/24/civilian-death-toll/|archive-date=2 November 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://sn4hr.org/blog/2018/09/24/females-victims-toll/|title=Females Victims Toll|accessdate=19 February 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181230025932/http://sn4hr.org/blog/2018/09/24/females-victims-toll/|archive-date=30 December 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://sn4hr.org/blog/2018/09/24/child-death-toll/|title=Child Death Toll|first=Syrian Network For Human|last=Rights|date=24 September 2019|publisher=|accessdate=24 September 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191103072902/http://sn4hr.org/blog/2018/09/24/child-death-toll/|archive-date=3 November 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Perpetrator\n! data-sort-type=number | Number of killed civilians\n! Men\n! Women\n! Children\n|-\n| Syrian government forces || 199,854 || 164,791 || 11,912 || 22,854\n|-\n| Russian forces || 6,851 || 3,678 || 968 || 2,005\n|-\n| Islamic State || 5,019 || 3,462 || 586 || 956\n|-\n| Other unnamed parties || 5,663 || 3,288 || 757 || 1,248\n|-\n| Other rebel forces || 4,136 || 2,273 || 874 || 985\n|-\n| International Coalition Forces || 3,039 || 1,457 || 656 || 924\n|-\n| Syrian Democratic Forces || 1,211 || 788 || 158 || 221\n|-\n| Hayat Tahrir al Sham || 470 || 317 || 76 || 66\n|-\n| Turkistan Islamic Party || 4 || 4 || 0 || 0\n|-\n| '''TOTAL''' || '''226,247''' || '''180,165''' || '''15,835''' || '''29,017'''\n|}\n\nAccording to the pro-opposition [[Syrian Observatory for Human Rights]], 116,086 civilians had been killed between March 2011 and mid-March 2020. This number does not include an estimated 88,000 civilians killed in government prisons.<ref name=SOHR/>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Perpetrator\n! data-sort-type=number | Number of killed civilians\n! Men\n! Women\n! Children\n|-\n| Syrian government forces || 87,952 || 60,607 || 10,353 || 16,992\n|-\n| Russian forces || 8,627 || 5,221 || 1,320 || 2,086\n|-\n| Opposition forces || 8,018 || 6,042 || 751 || 1,225\n|-\n| Islamic State || 6,204 || 5,281 || 400 || 523\n|-\n| International Coalition forces || 3,835 || 2,152 || 711 || 972\n|-\n| Turkish forces || 1,442 || 1,001 || 167 || 274\n|-\n| Israeli forces || 8 || 3 || 2 || 3\n|-\n| '''TOTAL''' || | '''116,086''' || '''80,307''' || '''13,704''' || '''22,075'''\n|}\n\n==Combatant deaths==\n\n===Government forces===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Pro-government combatants\n! Casualties\n|-\n|'''TOTAL'''\n|'''129,476-129,779''' killed<ref name=\"SOHR\"/><ref name=\"SOHR1\"/><ref name=\"balance\"/>\n|-\n|[[Syrian military]] and [[Ministry of Interior (Syria)|police]]\n|'''67,388''' killed<ref name=SOHR/><ref name=SOHR1>{{Cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=8103|title=Tantalizing promises of Bashar al- Assad kill more than 11000 fighters of his forces during 5 months.|last=|first=|date=17 December 2014|website=|publisher=SOHR|access-date=15 December 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161221005915/http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=8103|archive-date=21 December 2016|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[List of armed groups in the Syrian Civil War|Syrian militias]]\n|'''52,060''' killed<ref name=SOHR/><ref name=SOHR1/>\n|-\n|Lebanese [[Hezbollah]]\n|'''1,697\u20132,000''' killed<ref name=SOHR/><ref name=\"balance\">{{cite web|url=http://www.soufangroup.com/intelbrief-on-balance-hezbollah-has-benefited-from-the-syrian-conflict/|title=On Balance, Hezbollah Has Benefited from the Syrian Conflict|work=The Soufan Group|accessdate=17 September 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180917215556/http://www.soufangroup.com/intelbrief-on-balance-hezbollah-has-benefited-from-the-syrian-conflict/|archive-date=17 September 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Wagner Group#Casualties and awards|Russian PMCs]]\n|'''183\u2013283''' killed<ref>151\u2013201 killed (2015-17),[https://www.thedailybeast.com/a-russian-blackwater-putins-secret-soldiers-in-ukraine-and-syria][https://www.inopressa.ru/article/14Dec2017/spiegel/vagner01.html][https://news.vtomske.ru/news/150657-eshche-odin-dobrovolec-iz-tomskoi-oblasti-pogib-v-sirii] 14\u201364 killed ([[Battle of Khasham]], Feb. 2018),[https://www.pravda.ru/news/world/1371126-troshev/][https://ssu.gov.ua/en/news/1/category/2/view/5693#.NTRLLcQI.dpbs] 18 killed (May 2018-June 2019),[https://www.yahoo.com/news/26-syria-regime-9-russia-fighters-killed-attack-113110297.html][https://www.themoscowtimes.com/2018/11/06/six-russian-mercenaries-killed-syria-blast-reports-a63403][https://www.uawire.org/russian-officer-killed-in-syria][https://74.ru/text/incidents/66030364/][http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=125124][https://meduza.io/en/feature/2019/07/29/three-russian-mercenaries-are-killed-in-syria-and-they-re-not-from-the-pmc-you-ve-heard-of] total of 183\u2013283 reported dead</ref>\n|-\n|Other non-Syrian militiamen\n|'''8,067''' killed<ref name=SOHR/>\n|}\n\nThe non-Syrian militiamen fatalities figure includes: over 2,000 [[Liwa Fatemiyoun|Afghans]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.middleeasteye.net/news/more-2000-afghans-killed-syria-fighting-bashar-al-assad-official|title=More than 2,000 Afghans killed in Syria fighting for Bashar al-Assad: Official|website=Middle East Eye|accessdate=19 February 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190220063140/https://www.middleeasteye.net/news/more-2000-afghans-killed-syria-fighting-bashar-al-assad-official|archive-date=20 February 2019|url-status=live}}<br />[https://en.radiofarda.com/a/khamenei-praises-afghan-refugees-recruited-by-irgc-and-killed-in-syria-war/29850317.html Khamenei Praises Afghans Recruited By IRGC And Killed In Syria War] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330131123/https://en.radiofarda.com/a/khamenei-praises-afghan-refugees-recruited-by-irgc-and-killed-in-syria-war/29850317.html |date=2019-03-30 }}</ref> at least 1,308 [[Iraqi insurgency (Iraq War)#Shia Islamist|Iraqi Shia militiamen]],<ref>2 killed (2012),[https://www.washingtoninstitute.org/uploads/Documents/pubs/PolicyFocus138_Smyth-2.pdf] 1,200 (2013\u2013Feb. 2016),[https://www.alaraby.co.uk/english/news/2016/2/2/bodies-of-iraqis-killed-in-syria-received-in-baghdad] 12 killed (15 June 2016)[https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/southfront-70-islamist-rebels-killed-aftermath-southern-aleppo-clashes/] 13 killed (Aug. 2016),[https://twitter.com/Alfoneh/status/768304563728232453] 32\n(19\u201320 Dec. 2016),[http://en.eldorar.com/node/4094] 19 killed (March\u2013Aug. 2017),[https://twitter.com